Subject: RE: [VB] Dangerous Brakes!

Ironically, I had a system failure after traversing Mingus on the way TO
Jerome. I was pulling into my camping spot by Ronnie and the pedal went
all the way down. I grabbed the ebrake in time to avoid hitting his
(award-winning) Deluxe.

It turned out that I had done my Wolfgang spindle install incorrectly
and both front lines were rubbing on the kingpins. Bad move on my part.
I replaced both lines and redid the install so they would not rub. No
fault of anyone other than myself, but I can't say how blessed I felt
that it didn't happen on the way down the pass. I'd be a shiny spot on
the guardrail otherwise. All of the other parts are new on it, which I
can't recommend more...

Glad to hear that you remain safe.

~Rich
'60 DD Panel

